    "name": "James Blunt",
    "profile": "James Hillier Blount (born 22 February 1974 Tidworth, Wiltshire, England), better known by his stage name James Blunt, is an English singer-songwriter and former army officer, whose debut album, Back to Bedlam and single releases, including \"You're Beautiful\" and \"Goodbye My Lover\", brought him to fame in 2005. His repertoire can be best described as a mix of acoustic-tinged pop, rock and folk. After recording on the independent American label Custard Records, Blunt won two Brit Awards, two MTV Video Music Awards, two Ivor Novello Awards, and by 2006 was nominated for five Grammy Awards. The following year, he released his second album All the Lost Souls (2007). Blunt's third studio album, Some Kind of Trouble, was released in November 2010. Worldwide, Blunt has sold over 18 million albums, and his debut album, Back to Bedlam, is the best-selling album of the 2000s in the UK.\r\nBlunt was an officer in the Life Guards, a cavalry regiment of the British Army, and served under NATO in Koso",
